snippet.textDisplay:
I don't know where these people get their strength to be able to speak at a time like this let alone in front of the world. I am 53 years old and on 11/14/11 my baby sister died suddenly at 41 years old just two days shy of her 42nd birthday and 6 days after the birth of my daughter. My elderly parents were too devastated to speak and I was asked to step up, and I couldn't do it. I was so choked up with emotion I couldn't get a word out. My sisters 22 year old daughter gave her eulogy and I am so proud and in awe of the strength it took for her to speak at her mother's funeral.
Don't need any likes, not seeking attention. Just sharing a story in this time of sadness as it related to me.

Tell those you love that you love them as much as possible. You never know if you or they will have a tomorrow.

I wish I could tell my sister just one last time how much I loved her, how proud I was to be her big brother for 42 years, and that I miss her. She left a huge hole in our family. It's a shame when the birth of your daughter is over shadowed by the death of a family member. God gives, and God takes away.
I hope those who read this have an amazing day and even though I am just some random dude on YT....I love you too as a global citizen of humanity.

😥💜🙏
